# 2026-06-17 18:44:47.877637
+Act as a senior Product Designer and Next.js Frontend Engineer.
+
+Context
+
+The Programs Listing Page is already implemented.
+
+Current structure:
+
+* Hero
+* Spotlight Program
+* Live Now
+* Coming Soon
+* Explore Programs
+
+Components already exist:
+
+* ProgramCard
+* ProgramGrid
+* ProgramSection
+
+We are NOT adding:
+
+* search
+* filters
+* pagination
+* sorting
+* tabs
+* accordions
+
+Goal
+
+Refine the page to feel premium, editorial and content-first.
+
+This page should feel closer to:
+
+* Apple Events
+* Masterclass
+* Netflix Collections
+* Modern editorial publishing
+
+and less like:
+
+* conference software
+* webinar platform
+* admin dashboard
+* event management system
+
+Design Objectives
+
+1. Strong visual hierarchy
+
+The page should immediately communicate:
+
+* Featured experience
+* Currently active experiences
+* Discoverable program catalog
+
+2. More breathing room
+
+Review:
+
+* vertical rhythm
+* section spacing
+* content density
+* card spacing
+
+Prefer fewer elements with more space.
+
+3. Improve the Hero
+
+Review:
+
+* heading scale
+* width
+* typography
+* alignment
+
+The hero should introduce the page rather than explain it.
+
+4. Improve Spotlight Presentation
+
+The spotlight section should feel like the editorial centerpiece.
+
+Review:
+
+* image prominence
+* spacing
+* content hierarchy
+* CTA visibility
+
+5. Improve Program Cards
+
+Review:
+
+* information density
+* hierarchy
+* metadata placement
+
+Use the existing API fields:
+
+* brand
+* session_count
+* speaker_count
+* featured_session
+
+Help users quickly understand what the program contains.
+
+6. Improve Section Hierarchy
+
+Review ordering and visual weight of:
+
+* Spotlight
+* Live Now
+* Coming Soon
+* Explore Programs
+
+The page should guide the eye naturally.
+
+7. Responsive Review
+
+Review:
+
+* mobile experience
+* tablet experience
+* desktop experience
+
+Ensure the page feels intentional on all screen sizes.
+
+Implementation Constraints
+
+* Reuse existing design system
+* Reuse existing components
+* Do not introduce new dependencies
+* Do not add new features
+* Do not add filters
+* Do not add search
+* Do not add pagination
+
+Output
+
+1. UX critique of the current implementation
+2. Recommended improvements
+3. Specific code changes to make
+4. Prioritized list:
+
+   * Must Have
+   * Nice to Have
+   * Future Ideas
+
+Focus on refinement and presentation quality, not functionality.
+

# 2026-06-17 18:50:24.922752
+Act as a senior product designer and React engineer.
+
+Review the ProgramCard implementation.
+
+Do not redesign the component.
+
+Do not change the overall layout.
+
+Do not introduce new sections.
+
+Goal
+
+Refine the poster card hierarchy for content discovery.
+
+Current poster card displays:
+
+* brand
+* session count
+* program name
+* speaker count
+
+Problem
+
+Users can see the program title but cannot quickly understand what the program contains.
+
+The API already provides:
+
+program.featured_session?.name
+
+Requirements
+
+1. Surface featured_session.name in the poster card.
+
+Recommended hierarchy:
+
+Brand + Session Count
+
+Program Name
+
+Featured Session Label
+
+Featured Session Name
+
+Speaker Count
+
+2. Keep the card visually calm.
+
+Avoid:
+
+* descriptions
+* badges
+* additional metadata
+* extra icons
+
+3. Review spacing and typography hierarchy.
+
+The Program Name should remain the primary focal point.
+
+Featured Session should be secondary.
+
+Speaker Count should remain tertiary.
+
+4. Review mobile layout.
+
+Ensure the card still feels balanced when the featured session name wraps onto two lines.
+
+5. Do not modify the spotlight card unless there is a strong UX reason.
+
+Output:
+
+* UX critique
+* Recommended refinements
+* Exact code changes
+* Explanation of why the hierarchy improves discoverability

