# 2026-06-17 19:49:06.441253
+Act as a senior Next.js engineer and product designer.
+
+Context
+
+The Programs Listing Page is complete.
+
+We are now implementing the Program Details Page.
+
+Important
+
+Assume the backend endpoint is already implemented and working.
+
+GET /api/v2/storefront/programs/:slug
+
+Frontend only.
+
+Follow the same patterns already used in the project for:
+
+* Product Details Page
+
+Review the existing codebase and follow the established conventions.
+
+Tasks
+
+STEP 1 — Implement API Client
+
+Create the frontend API request for Program Details.
+
+Follow the same approach used by:
+
+* getProduct(...)
+
+Do not invent a new API layer.
+
+Reuse the existing fetch helpers and response patterns.
+
+Implement:
+
+getProgram(slug)
+
+Assume the API response shape is:
+
+{
+program,
+stats,
+featured_session,
+speakers,
+sessions
+}
+
+STEP 2 — Implement Program Details Page
+
+Implement:
+
+app/(storefront)/programs/[slug]/page.tsx
+
+Focus on UX and presentation.
+
+Program = Collection Page
+
+Session = Content Page
+
+The Program page should feel closer to:
+
+* Netflix Series Page
+* Apple Event Page
+* Masterclass Course Page
+
+and less like:
+
+* Conference Agenda
+* Webinar Schedule
+* Event Management Software
+
+Information Architecture
+
+Identity
+↓
+Entry Point
+↓
+Content
+↓
+Context
+
+Page Structure
+
+1. Hero
+
+Show:
+
+* cover image
+* brand
+* program name
+* description
+* session count
+* speaker count
+
+Primary CTA
+
+Start Watching →
+
+CTA destination:
+
+featured_session
+
+fallback:
+
+first session
+
+Do NOT create a separate Featured Session section.
+
+The Hero CTA is the entry point.
+
+2. Sessions
+
+Most important section.
+
+Render immediately after the Hero.
+
+Adaptive Layout
+
+If sessions.length === 1
+
+* single large session card
+
+If sessions.length between 2 and 5
+
+* responsive 2-column grid
+
+If sessions.length >= 6
+
+* responsive 3-column grid
+
+Each session card should display:
+
+* thumbnail
+* session type
+* session name
+* speaker names (if available)
+* media type
+* status
+
+Each card links to:
+
+/programs/[program_slug]/sessions/[session_slug]
+
+Do NOT render:
+
+* timelines
+* schedules
+* agendas
+* calendars
+
+3. Speakers
+
+Render lightweight speaker cards.
+
+Show:
+
+* avatar
+* name
+* title
+* company
+
+4. About Program
+
+Render:
+
+* program description
+
+Optionally display:
+
+* session count
+* speaker count
+
+Desktop:
+two-column layout
+
+Mobile:
+stacked layout
+
+5. More From Brand
+
+Placeholder section only.
+
+No API integration yet.
+
+Reuse existing ProgramCard.
+
+Implementation Constraints
+
+* Reuse existing design system
+* Reuse existing Section
+* Reuse existing Container
+* Reuse existing Typography components
+* Reuse existing Grid where appropriate
+* Follow existing storefront patterns
+
+Do NOT create new reusable abstractions yet.
+
+Do NOT create:
+
+* ProgramHero
+* ProgramSessions
+* ProgramSpeakers
+* ProgramAbout
+
+Build the page directly first.
+
+Output
+
+1. Files to create or modify
+2. API client implementation
+3. Program Details page implementation
+4. Any frontend assumptions made about the API response

